i## Is it worth it?	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iReading and putting LFS into practice takes a long time, but	/	tilde.team	70
iit's definitely worth it! I was able to learn some very	/	tilde.team	70
iinteresting and useful new things about the world of Linux	/	tilde.team	70
iand now I understand more precisely how Linux and UNIX	/	tilde.team	70
isystems work.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iI recommend the experience to all curious people who want to	/	tilde.team	70
ihave their own Linux system. The result is very satisfying,	/	tilde.team	70
iand it's even possible to use an LFS system as your main	/	tilde.team	70
isystem!	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Conclusion	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iI loved reading the book and setting up everything myself,	/	tilde.team	70
iand I intend to keep my LFS system and continue modifying	/	tilde.team	70
iit.	/	tilde.team	70
